article.description: Joseph Chartouny scored 14 points, Javontae Hawkins added 11 and Fordham beat Saint Peter's 63-41 on Saturday night in the Johnny Bach Classic.
article.headline: Fordham beats Saint Peter's 63-41 in Johnny Bach Classic
article.linkText: Fordham beats Saint Peter's 63-41 in Johnny Bach Classic
article.story: NEW YORK -- Joseph Chartouny scored 14 points, Javontae Hawkins added 11 and Fordham beat Saint Peter's 63-41 on Saturday night in the Johnny Bach Classic. Chartouny also had four steals as Fordham forced 26 turnovers. The Rams had a 33-20 lead at halftime and started the second half on an 8-0 run -- with six combined points from Chartouny and Hawkins -- for a 41-20 lead. Fordham built a 33-point lead after Prokop Slanina hit a 3-pointer with 9:20 left. Christian Sengfelder and Antwoine Anderson scored eight points each for Fordham (3-1). The Rams made 8 of 25 3-pointers but were held to 40 percent shooting overall. Quadir Welton led Saint Peter's (1-2) with 10 points and four blocks. The Peacocks were 2 of 16 from 3-point range and made just 35 percent from the field.
